snippet.textDisplay: I am not here to comment about which party is right or wrong. What I feel bad for is that Novak had history on the line as this could have been very well his 21st gs and it would have put him ahead of roger and rafa. At least for this reason, I think he should have just went along with it, taken the jab, played the tournament and won the 21st. Not saying he cannot win his 21st at the French but he has better % of winning the aus than the french and I also feel at this stage of their careers, the big 3 should have to give themselves as many shots at the title to get ahead of each other. Now he had given a free pass to Nadal (Not saying Nadal would win the tournament) and he had deprived himself of a chance to get ahead of the other 2.

snippet.textDisplay:
Djokovic's series of mistakes:
1. Didn't simply get vaccinated for Australian Open while most athletes did.
2. After was granted visa on exemption publicly anounced on Instagram which meant he wasn't vaccinated. This provoked the Australian government indeed.
3. He assumed that there is clear law in Australia and courts are here to look after people's rights 
4. Djokovic's biggest mistake: after the first court he didn't take the initiative to leave Australia before getting deported. It was obvious that the he would be deported. If he had left before getting deported he could apply for visa any time later but now he can't enter Australia for 3 years. In addition he has to pay the legal costs.Not sure if he got a second opinion in addition to his lawyer's opinion.

Update: I'm an unvaccinated person and I don't think vaccines prevent transmitting. The Australian government website clearly says there is no proven link between vaccine and ability to transmit. We know it's all political after all.
